{"word":"εὐφραίνω","slug":"εὐφραίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐφραίνω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to cheer, delight, gladden</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to make merry, enjoy oneself, be happy</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>ἐπί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>ἔν τινι, διά τινος, ἀπό τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a>, <el>εὐφράνθη ἰδών</el> <i>was rejoiced at</i> seeing, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}